com.delicious.deliciousfeeds4J

Class DeliciousFeeds

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.delicious.deliciousfeeds4J.DeliciousFeeds

  • public class DeliciousFeeds
extends java.lang.Object
    DeliciousFeeds is a class to access the Feeds-API from Delicious. It uses the current version 2 of it: Feeds-API Documentation v2
    Author:
    Patrick Meier

      • findBookmarksByUrl

        public java.util.List<Bookmark> findBookmarksByUrl(int count,
                                          java.lang.String url)
                                            throws DeliciousFeedsException
        Find bookmarks on delicious for a specific url.

        Important! Delicious seems to multiply the given count by 10! So a given count of 1 actually yields 10 bookmarks!

        Parameters:
        count - how many entries should be returned (value is multiplied by 10!) - from 1 to 100
        url - the url
        Returns:
        a list of bookmarks for this url, null if nothing found!
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if count does not match borders or url is null or empty
        DeliciousFeedsException - if something goes wrong

      • getUserAgent

        public java.lang.String getUserAgent()
        Gets the current UserAgent used for requests.
        Returns:
        userAgent current UserAgent

      • setUserAgent

        public void setUserAgent(java.lang.String userAgent)
        Sets the UserAgent for the requests. Takes effect immediately on the next request taken.

        It is highly recommended to set this value to a real UserAgent (e.g. "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.2; Win64; x64; rv:16.0.1)"), because otherwise you may get blocked by yahoo (as written in the api-doc!)

        Parameters:
        userAgent - the UserAgent to use

      • isExpandUrls

        public boolean isExpandUrls()
        Gets whether the shortened delicious urls should be expanded. By default this is false.

        This maybe time consuming to use. For every bookmark another request is made!

        Returns:
        expandUrls if shortened urls should be expanded

      • setExpandUrls

        public void setExpandUrls(boolean expandUrls)
        Sets whether the shortened delicious urls should be expanded. By default this is false.

        This maybe time consuming to use. For every bookmark another request is made!

        Parameters:
        expandUrls - if shortened urls should be expanded

      • isConstainAPILimit

        public boolean isConstainAPILimit()
        Sets if you want to constrain the API limit. If so there is a pause between each request of 1 second. By default this is true.

        Important! If you set this to false you risk to get banned!

        Returns:
        if you want to contrain the API limit

      • setConstainAPILimit

        public void setConstainAPILimit(boolean constainAPILimit)
        Sets if you want to constrain the API limit. If so there is a pause between each request of 1 second. By default this is true.

        Important! If you set this to false you risk to get banned!

        Parameters:
        constainAPILimit - if you want to contrain the API limit
